                                <div id="faq18" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="faqHead18"
                                    data-parent="#accordionExample">
                                    <div class="card-body">
                                    <p>HBA members can list their products in three different ways, <i>Auction</i>, <i>Fixed
                                        Price</i>, and <i>Make An Offer listings</i>.</p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>
                                        <u>Auction/Minimum-Bid Auction:</u> The seller pre-determines the lowest
                                        acceptable price (reserve price). The seller may post a lower starting price to
                                        get the auction ball rolling. However, if the reserve price is not met, the
                                        product does not sell.
                                        A seller may also offer a <u>Buy Now</u> price option with a minimum order
                                        quantity of product. If a portion of the auction product listing is sold with
                                        the <u>Buy Now</u> option, the listing will automatically become a <u>Fixed
                                            Price</u> listing. The seller may then go into their dashboard and relist
                                        his product as a new auction with the new inventory level or keep it as a
                                        <u>Fixed Price</u> listing.
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <u>Fixed Price:</u> A <u>Fixed Price</u> listing is used when the seller knows
                                        his acceptable fixed sale price on his product/s.
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <u>Make An Offer:</u> A seller may post a product with a suggested offer price.
                                        He may entertain all offers that come in but is only obligated to sell at the
                                        “Offer Price”. They may choose to accept or not accept any other offer..
