                                <p>Buyer selects item to purchase → Buyer & Seller agree to transaction initial terms →
                                    Transaction Coordinator makes introduction via recorded conference call → SOPs,
                                    Samples, quarantine, purchase contract, logistics/insurance are discussed and agreed
                                    upon → Purchase contract is completed by both parties → purchase contract is
                                    uploaded into system → Buyer sends funds to HBA → Product is transported per terms
                                    of the agreement/contract executed → Buyer receives the product → HBA pays the
                                    seller</p>

                                <h3>LIFECYCLE OF TRANSACTIONS > $15,001.00</h3>
                                <p>Buyer selects item to purchase → Buyer & Seller agree to transaction initial terms →
                                    Transaction Coordinator makes introduction via recorded conference call→ SOPs,
                                    Samples, quarantine, purchase contract, logistics/insurance are discussed and agreed
                                    upon → Purchase contract is executed by both parties → purchase contract is uploaded
                                    into system → Seller chooses escrow/attorney service → Transaction Coordinator sends
                                    transaction details to designated escrow/attorneys → Escrow is opened → Buyer
                                    deposit funds into escrow → Escrow/Attorney verifies the funds → Product is
                                    transported per terms of the agreement → Buyer receives the product → Escrow pays
                                    the seller</p>

