                    <div class="media-body" id='glossory'>
                        <h1>Glossary of Terms</h1>
                        <h3>Start price</h3>
                        <p>The likely starting bid for a given auction, set by the seller at the time of listing.</p>

                        <h3>Reserve price</h3>
                        <p>A reserve price is a minimum price a seller is willing to accept from a buyer. In an auction,
                            the seller is not required to disclose the reserve price to potential buyers. If the reserve
                            price is not met, the seller is not required to sell the item, even to the highest bidder.
                        </p>

                        <h3>Authorized Representative</h3>
                        <p>Someone who you choose to act on your behalf within the HBA Auction/Market. The authorized
                            representative has the legal authority to act on your behalf.
                            <a href="https://docs.hempbuyer.com/authorized-business-representative-form/">Download a
                                Authorized Business Representative Form Here</a>

                        <div class="text-center w-100 mt-3 mb-3"><b>Examples:</b></div>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Registered member/broker using an authorized representative agreement to sell materials
                                on behalf of other registered members.</li>
                            <li>Cooperative representative who has the legal authority to represent and transact
                                business on behalf of the registered cooperative members behalf.</li>
                            <li>Principle, employee or representative of a company authorized to transact business on
                                behalf of a registered company member. </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>

                    <div class="media-body" id='escrow'>
                        <h1>Escrow - How it works </h1>
                        <p>Escrow is a financial instrument held by an independent third party on behalf of the two
                            other parties who are completing a transaction. It’s like a trust account held by a third
                            party while all the seller and buyer’s obligations are fulfilled. All the details of the
                            contract are completed and fulfilled, then funds are released to the seller. </p>
